The group also said that the UK government has now pledged funds to improve the nutrition of mothers and children after receiving more than 5,000 online calls. This project, Power of Nutrition, will help five million mothers and children with advice on nutrition.
In response to one of the website's frequently asked questions, which says, "What makes you think that we can end extreme poverty?"
Global Citizen wrote: "It will be a long and hard fight, and sometimes we will stumble and make mistakes.
But like the civil rights movement and the movements against apartheid, we will succeed because we are stronger together."
